    <item>
      <title>TypeScript Best Practices for 2024</title>
      <link>https://florianheiwig.de/technical/frontend/typescript-best-practices/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 15 Jan 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://florianheiwig.de/technical/frontend/typescript-best-practices/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;introduction&#34;&gt;Introduction&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;TypeScript has evolved significantly over the years. Here are the patterns and practices I&amp;rsquo;ve found most valuable in 2024.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;type-safety-fundamentals&#34;&gt;Type Safety Fundamentals&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Getting the basics right is crucial for a healthy TypeScript codebase.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;strict-mode-is-non-negotiable&#34;&gt;Strict Mode is Non-Negotiable&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Always enable strict mode in your tsconfig. Yes, it&amp;rsquo;s more work initially, but it catches bugs before they reach production.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-json&#34; data-lang=&#34;json&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;{&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;compilerOptions&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;: {&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;strict&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;,&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;noImplicitAny&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;,&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;    &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;strictNullChecks&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  }&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;}&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id=&#34;prefer-interfaces-for-objects&#34;&gt;Prefer Interfaces for Objects&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Use interfaces for object shapes and types for unions and primitives. This isn&amp;rsquo;t just stylisticâ€”interfaces have better error messages and are more extensible.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>React State Management in 2024: What Actually Works</title>
      <link>https://florianheiwig.de/technical/frontend/react-state-management/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 08 Jan 2024 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://florianheiwig.de/technical/frontend/react-state-management/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;introduction&#34;&gt;Introduction&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The React ecosystem has more state management solutions than you can count. Let&amp;rsquo;s cut through the noise and talk about what actually works in production.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;the-state-management-spectrum&#34;&gt;The State Management Spectrum&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Not all state is created equal. Understanding the different types of state helps you choose the right tool:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;local-component-state&#34;&gt;Local Component State&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;For state that only one component needs, &lt;code&gt;useState&lt;/code&gt; is still king:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-tsx&#34; data-lang=&#34;tsx&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;function&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;Counter() {&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;const&lt;/span&gt; [&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;count&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;setCount&lt;/span&gt;] &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;useState&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;0&lt;/span&gt;);&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;  &lt;span style=&#34;color:#66d9ef&#34;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &amp;lt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;button&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;onClick&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;{() &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;setCount&lt;/span&gt;(&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;c&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;=&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;c&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;+&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#ae81ff&#34;&gt;1&lt;/span&gt;)}&amp;gt;{&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;count&lt;/span&gt;}&amp;lt;/&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;button&lt;/span&gt;&amp;gt;;&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;}&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Don&amp;rsquo;t overcomplicate this. If it&amp;rsquo;s local, keep it local.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
